abstract: French authorities finish dismantling southern half of migrant camp in Calais, prompting question of where those who lived there will go; humanitarian groups say most migrants are resisting move to state-sanctioned centers and simply moving to northern half of camp.

headline.print_headline: As France Razes Camp, Some Question Where Migrants Will Go
headline.main: As France Razes Calais Camp, Some Ask Where Migrants Will Go

keywords.value: Middle East and Africa Migrant Crisis
keywords.name: subject

snippet: Workers finished dismantling part of the so-called Jungle camp, but many migrants have resisted relocation to state-sanctioned centers.
